<subSubSection id="C355653DFFBA8D22F01CA04391F8B7CE" pageId="4" pageNumber="155" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="8BF036B6FFBA8D22F01CA04391F8B7CE" blockId="4.[103,1309,1444,2656]" pageId="4" pageNumber="155">
<emphasis id="B93BEAA4FFBA8D22F01CA04390CBB743" bold="true" box="[105,452,2347,2380]" pageId="4" pageNumber="155">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Data Deficient on The IUCN Red List. The Noble Brush-tailed Mouse is known from only a few localities on Mount Damavand and in the Central Alborz Mountains of northern Iran. No conservation threats have been identified.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
